{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"This is not a bug in the three.js animation system. Seems that there went something wrong with the export to JSON (wrong settings?).\r\n\r\nthree.js does exactly what the JSON file says: There are keyframes for each bone in both animation hierarchies. Hence the legs are reset in the throw animation, and the arms are rotated to horizontal position in the idle animation (BTW: Wouldn't it be better \u201cwalk\u201d instead of \u201cidle\u201d?).\r\n\r\nHere is a JSON file in which I've simply emptied these keys for testing purposes: [player.zip](https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/files\/1057397\/player.zip). It works as expected. \r\n","created_at":"2017-06-07T08:51:55.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11455#issuecomment-306732508","id":306732508,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11455","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNjczMjUwOA==","updated_at":"2017-06-07T10:35:12.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/306732508","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/5700294?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/jostschmithals","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU3MDAyOTQ=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"jostschmithals","type":"User","id":5700294,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@jostschmithals Okay I see. What settings should be used with the exporter to ensure a proper .json file is created?\r\n\r\nAlso, yeah it would make more since to have the idle animation be a walk animation but I was just making some easy animations to simplify the problem, didn't think about it too much.","created_at":"2017-06-08T00:15:06.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11455#issuecomment-306962050","id":306962050,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11455","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNjk2MjA1MA==","updated_at":"2017-06-08T00:15:06.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/306962050","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/KyleNBurke\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/KyleNBurke\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/11780151?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/KyleNBurke","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/KyleNBurke\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/KyleNBurke","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/KyleNBurke\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExNzgwMTUx","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/KyleNBurke\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/KyleNBurke\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/KyleNBurke\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"KyleNBurke","type":"User","id":11780151,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/KyleNBurke\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/KyleNBurke\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"I have no detailed experience with blender. So I only wanted to isolate the problem saying that it can\u2019t be a bug in the three.js animation system, but must have to do something with the blender source or the exporter.\r\n\r\nIt could be \r\n- that your source file is not completely valid (it is quite common that problems, e.g. caused by a non-proper reset of the model before rigging, don\u2019t occur already in the modeling software but only in the software to which the model is exported), \r\n- or that the export settings have to be adjusted (?), \r\n- or that the reason is a bug in the exporter.\r\n\r\nPerhaps it would be the best if you close this issue, ask on http:\/\/discourse.threejs.org\/ or stackoverflow, or, if this doesn't help and you assume it is an exporter bug, create a new bug report issue with a blender exporter related title.\r\n","created_at":"2017-06-08T19:18:03.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11455#issuecomment-307201005","id":307201005,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11455","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNzIwMTAwNQ==","updated_at":"2017-06-08T19:18:03.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/307201005","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jostschmithals\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/5700294?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jost